  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "ESM measures the matched SQL keywords between the predicted SQL query and its corresponding ground truth SQL query (YU et al., 2018b).",
    "EA, on the other hand, compares the execution output of the predicted SQL query with that of the ground truth SQL query on some database instances (GAO et al., 2023).",
    "There are metrics designed to assess the efficiency of valid SQLs generated by models.",
    "Valid Efficiency Score (VES), proposed by Li et al. (2023), aims at quantifying the efficiency of the SQL generated by LLM, that is, running time, throughput, memory cost, or merged metrics.",
    "Most of the LLM-based Text-to-SQL tools (POURREZA; RAFIEI, 2023; DONG et al., 2023b; GAO et al., 2023; GUO et al., 2023b) and benchmarks (YU et al., 2018b; LI et al., 2023; LAN et al., 2023) have EA as a metric."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
